    "comment": "Rationale: Tpd52 is present in FASS-sorted, VGluT1Venus-containing synaptosomes.\n\nSubcellular fractionation revealed Tpd52 to be strongly enriched in the synaptic cytosol fraction (LS2, Fig.6H). Immunocytochemistry of cultured hippocampal neurons revealed colocalization with VGluT1, PSD-95 and MAP2 immunoreactivity (Fig.6J,K and S4).\n\nAntibody: Tpd52 (1:250; Shehata et al, 2008): Membranes were washed twice with TBS and incubated with affinity-purified rabbit polyclonal D52 antisera (1:100). No specific information on the antibody or the specificity.. Experimental description: Briefly, forebrains of one or two mice were homogenized...",
